to the message body.','User message sent alongside the artwork image. Use {artist_prompt} where the artist\'s own description should appear.'=>'User message sent alongside the artwork image. Use {artist_prompt} where the artist\'s own description should appear.','Username or email address'=>'Username or email address','Verification failed. Please try again.'=>'Verification failed. Please try again.','View Agnosis details'=>'View Agnosis details','View Artwork'=>'View Artwork','View Biography'=>'View Biography','View details'=>'View details','View Event'=>'View Event','View it live'=>'View it live','View it online.'=>'View it online.','View Post'=>'View Post','View submissions →'=>'View submissions →','Vision image max width (px)'=>'Vision image max width (px)','Visit plugin site'=>'Visit plugin site','Visitor-to-artist contact messages (sent or rejected) older than this are permanently deleted by the daily cleanup. The visitor\'s IP address is cleared independently after 30 days regardless of this setting, once it\'s no longer useful for abuse investigation. Default: 90 days.'=>'Visitor-to-artist contact messages (sent or rejected) older than this are permanently deleted by the daily cleanup. The visitor\'s IP address is cleared independently after 30 days regardless of this setting, once it\'s no longer useful for abuse investigation. Default: 90 days.','Visitors can still reach you through the contact form on your page.'=>'Visitors can still reach you through the contact form on your page.','Visitors subscribe via the agnosis/newsletter-signup block (double opt-in). Digest: new artwork and events published since the last issue.'=>'Visitors subscribe via the agnosis/newsletter-signup block (double opt-in). Digest: new artwork and events published since the last issue.','Vote'=>'Vote','Vote against this application?'=>'Vote against this application?','Vote error'=>'Vote error','Vote in favor of this application?'=>'Vote in favor of this application?','Vote NO'=>'Vote NO','Vote NO (keep)'=>'Vote NO (keep)','Vote recorded'=>'Vote recorded','Vote to keep this artist in the community?'=>'Vote to keep this artist in the community?','Vote to remove this artist from the community?'=>'Vote to remove this artist from the community?','Vote YES'=>'Vote YES','Vote YES (remove)'=>'Vote YES (remove)','Voter account not found.'=>'Voter account not found.','Votes'=>'Votes','Voting window (days)'=>'Voting window (days)','Voting window: %d day(s).'=>'Voting window: %d day(s).','Vouch messages you wrote were redacted. Governance votes you cast were kept as-is — a vote is a community record, not personal data, and removing it would silently change a settled decision.'=>'Vouch messages you wrote were redacted. Governance votes you cast were kept as-is — a vote is a community record, not personal data, and removing it would silently change a settled decision.','Want to tweak the title, text or tags before publishing?'=>'Want to tweak the title, text or tags before publishing?','We detected some photographic issues and applied AI correction to improve visibility of your artwork:'=>'We detected some photographic issues and applied AI correction to improve visibility of your artwork:','We received a removal request for "%s", but couldn\'t find an artwork or event with that exact title in your account.'=>'We received a removal request for "%s", but couldn\'t find an artwork or event with that exact title in your account.','We received a removal request for the following %s:'=>'We received a removal request for the following %s:','We received a removal request, but more than one of your posts shares that exact title. Choose which one you meant below — each is independent, so removing one leaves the others untouched.'=>'We received a removal request, but more than one of your posts shares that exact title. Choose which one you meant below — each is independent, so removing one leaves the others untouched.','We received a request to feature "%s", but couldn\'t find a published artwork with that exact title in your account.'=>'We received a request to feature "%s", but couldn\'t find a published artwork with that exact title in your account.','We received a request to remove your account and all your published work from %s.'=>'We received a request to remove your account and all your published work from %s.','We received your application to %s'=>'We received your application to %s','We received your email, but couldn\'t process a usable photo, audio, or video file from it — so nothing was published. This can happen when an image is pasted or inserted inline rather than added as a proper attachment, or when a file arrives in a format this server can\'t convert (for example, an iPhone photo saved in HEIC/HEIF format).'=>'We received your email, but couldn\'t process a usable photo, audio, or video file from it — so nothing was published. This can happen when an image is pasted or inserted inline rather than added as a proper attachment, or when a file arrives in a format this server can\'t convert (for example, an iPhone photo saved in HEIC/HEIF format).','We received your email, but it looked like a reply or a forwarded message — carrying quoted text from an earlier email. We looked for your own original text or an attachment above the quoted part, but couldn\'t find anything to work with, so nothing was published.'=>'We received your email, but it looked like a reply or a forwarded message — carrying quoted text from an earlier email. We looked for your own original text or an attachment above the quoted part, but couldn\'t find anything to work with, so nothing was published.','We received your submission, but unfortunately the photo quality is too low for us to show your artwork clearly. We didn\'t publish it — but please don\'t be discouraged! A simple retake is usually all it takes.'=>'We received your submission, but unfortunately the photo quality is too low for us to show your artwork clearly. We didn\'t publish it — but please don\'t be discouraged! A simple retake is usually all it takes.','Webhook request timestamp is missing, malformed, or too old.'=>'Webhook request timestamp is missing, malformed, or too old.','Webhook secret'=>'Webhook secret','Webhook secret not configured.'=>'Webhook secret not configured.','Welcome to %s'=>'Welcome to %s','Welcome to our newest member: %s'=>'Welcome to our newest member: %s' . "\0" . 'Welcome to our newest members: %s','What personal data we collect and why'=>'What personal data we collect and why','When enabled, a link to a site not on the trusted list above is not simply discarded: the destination page is fetched and reviewed by your configured AI provider (Settings → AI Providers) against the categories below before deciding whether to embed it. If the AI cannot be reached, the request times out, or the page cannot be safely fetched, the link is not embedded — it fails safe. When disabled (the default), only the trusted platforms above are ever embedded.'=>'When enabled, a link to a site not on the trusted list above is not simply discarded: the destination page is fetched and reviewed by your configured AI provider (Settings → AI Providers) against the categories below before deciding whether to embed it. If the AI cannot be reached, the request times out, or the page cannot be safely fetched, the link is not embedded — it fails safe. When disabled (the default), only the trusted platforms above are ever embedded.','When enabled, Agnosis drafts an intro via AI ahead of each issue (see the lead time below), saves it to that newsletter\'s intro field, and emails you to review it — unless you\'ve already written one for that cycle. Disable to leave both intro fields exactly as you left them, always.'=>'When enabled, Agnosis drafts an intro via AI ahead of each issue (see the lead time below), saves it to that newsletter\'s intro field, and emails you to review it — unless you\'ve already written one for that cycle. Disable to leave both intro fields exactly as you left them, always.','When enabled, biography submissions are passed through the AI to fix spelling and make minor text improvements before saving.'=>'When enabled, biography submissions are passed through the AI to fix spelling and make minor text improvements before saving.','When enabled, biography updates are merged with the existing biography using AI — new information is integrated rather than replacing everything. Recommended: artists can send incremental updates ("I just won an award") without resubmitting their full bio. Disable to always replace the biography with the latest submission.'=>'When enabled, biography updates are merged with the existing biography using AI — new information is integrated rather than replacing everything. Recommended: artists can send incremental updates ("I just won an award") without resubmitting their full bio. Disable to always replace the biography with the latest submission.','When enabled, event submissions are passed through the AI to fix spelling and make minor text improvements before saving.'=>'When enabled, event submissions are passed through the AI to fix spelling and make minor text improvements before saving.','When enabled, intake messages must pass SPF or DKIM authentication (via the Authentication-Results header). Prevents spoofed From: addresses. Requires your ESP to include Authentication-Results headers and your domain to have SPF/DKIM records configured. Leave off if you are not sure — rejected legitimate mail is silent. Default: off.'=>'When enabled, intake messages must pass SPF or DKIM authentication (via the Authentication-Results header). Prevents spoofed From: addresses. Requires your ESP to include Authentication-Results headers and your domain to have SPF/DKIM records configured. Leave off if you are not sure — rejected legitimate mail is silent. Default: off.','When set, every artist\'s biography page uses this exact title instead of their own, regardless of what the artist submitted, edited on their approve form, or later changed on their published page. Leave blank to keep using each artist\'s own title (the default). Shown exactly as typed here on every language version of a biography page — not machine-translated per language. See "Include artist\'s name in preset title" below.'=>'When set, every artist\'s biography page uses this exact title instead of their own, regardless of what the artist submitted, edited on their approve form, or later changed on their published page. Leave blank to keep using each artist\'s own title (the default). Shown exactly as typed here on every language version of a biography page — not machine-translated per language. See "Include artist\'s name in preset title" below.','When the preset title above is set, append the artist\'s own WordPress display name to it (e.g. "Meet the Artist — Jane Doe"). Has no effect while the preset title is blank.'=>'When the preset title above is set, append the artist\'s own WordPress display name to it (e.g. "Meet the Artist — Jane Doe"). Has no effect while the preset title is blank.','When you apply to join, we store your email address, display name, biography, statement, and portfolio link to run the community vouching process. When you email us artwork, a biography, or an event, the content of that email (including your address) is stored while it is processed and reviewed. When you subscribe to our newsletter or message an artist through their contact form, we store your email address (and, for contact messages, your IP address) to deliver that message or send you future issues.'=>'When you apply to join, we store your email address, display name, biography, statement, and portfolio link to run the community vouching process. When you email us artwork, a biography, or an event, the content of that email (including your address) is stored while it is processed and reviewed. When you subscribe to our newsletter or message an artist through their contact form, we store your email address (and, for contact messages, your IP address) to deliver that message or send you future issues.','Who we share it with'=>'Who we share it with','Why do you want to join?'=>'Why do you want to join?','Width of the agnosis-artwork image size used in post content and lightbox. Height scales proportionally. Default: 1920. Existing images need to be regenerated after changing this value.'=>'Width of the agnosis-artwork image size used in post content and lightbox. Height scales proportionally. Default: 1920. Existing images need to be regenerated after changing this value.','Width of the agnosis-email size used in artist notification emails. Height scales proportionally — no cropping. Default: 420. Existing images need to be regenerated after changing this value.'=>'Width of the agnosis-email size used in artist notification emails. Height scales proportionally — no cropping. Default: 420. Existing images need to be regenerated after changing this value.','Width of the card every outgoing HTML email is built around. 600px is the long-standing email-safe default most clients render reliably — narrower reads awkwardly on desktop, wider risks getting clipped or horizontally scrolled by some mobile mail apps. Default: 600.'=>'Width of the card every outgoing HTML email is built around. 600px is the long-standing email-safe default most clients render reliably — narrower reads awkwardly on desktop, wider risks getting clipped or horizontally scrolled by some mobile mail apps. Default: 600.','WordPress AI Client'=>'WordPress AI Client','WordPress AI Client is available and a text-generation model is configured.'=>'WordPress AI Client is available and a text-generation model is configured.','WordPress AI Client requires WordPress 7.0 or later.'=>'WordPress AI Client requires WordPress 7.0 or later.','wp_mail() reported a failure — check your site\'s outgoing mail configuration.'=>'wp_mail() reported a failure — check your site\'s outgoing mail configuration.','Write about this artwork…'=>'Write about this artwork…','Writes raw diagnostic dumps of the email intake pipeline (message structure, attachment MIME detection, media conversion, post creation) to a dedicated debug directory — far more detail than the Logs tab keeps, for tracing exactly where a submission was rejected or lost. Turn off once you have what you need; files can accumulate quickly. Can also be forced from wp-config.php with `define( \'AGNOSIS_DEBUG\', true );`, which overrides this toggle. See the Debug Files panel below for the directory location and a clear-files button.'=>'Writes raw diagnostic dumps of the email intake pipeline (message structure, attachment MIME detection, media conversion, post creation) to a dedicated debug directory — far more detail than the Logs tab keeps, for tracing exactly where a submission was rejected or lost. Turn off once you have what you need; files can accumulate quickly. Can also be forced from wp-config.php with `define( \'AGNOSIS_DEBUG\', true );`, which overrides this toggle. See the Debug Files panel below for the directory location and a clear-files button.','Yes, discard it'=>'Yes, discard it','Yes, remove it'=>'Yes, remove it','Yes, remove this %s'=>'Yes, remove this %s','Yes, remove this instead'=>'Yes, remove this instead','You are already an admitted Agnosis artist.'=>'You are already an admitted Agnosis artist.','You are welcome to apply again in the future.'=>'You are welcome to apply again in the future.','You can change your vote at any time within the voting window.'=>'You can change your vote at any time within the voting window.','You cannot nominate yourself for removal.'=>'You cannot nominate yourself for removal.','You cannot vote on your own application.'=>'You cannot vote on your own application.','You cannot vote on your own removal.'=>'You cannot vote on your own removal.','You do not have permission to perform this action.'=>'You do not have permission to perform this action.','You do not have permission to review this submission.'=>'You do not have permission to review this submission.','You have %1$d confirmed public subscribers, above the configured comfort threshold of %2$d. Self-hosted sending still works, but you may want to connect an email service provider (e.g. Brevo\'s free tier) for better deliverability at this size.'=>'You have %1$d confirmed public subscribers, above the configured comfort threshold of %2$d. Self-hosted sending still works, but you may want to connect an email service provider (e.g. Brevo\'s free tier) for better deliverability at this size.','You have left'=>'You have left','You may only edit your own content.'=>'You may only edit your own content.','You must be logged in.'=>'You must be logged in.','You voted against this application.'=>'You voted against this application.','You voted in favor of this application.'=>'You voted in favor of this application.','You voted to keep this artist in the community.'=>'You voted to keep this artist in the community.','You voted to remove this artist from the community.'=>'You voted to remove this artist from the community.','You will be automatically reinstated on that date.'=>'You will be automatically reinstated on that date.','You will no longer receive the artist newsletter. You can re-subscribe any time from your submissions page.'=>'You will no longer receive the artist newsletter. You can re-subscribe any time from your submissions page.','You will no longer receive the newsletter. Sorry to see you go.'=>'You will no longer receive the newsletter. Sorry to see you go.','You will stop receiving the newsletter once you confirm below.'=>'You will stop receiving the newsletter once you confirm below.','You\'ll continue to receive community broadcasts.'=>'You\'ll continue to receive community broadcasts.','You\'ll receive an email as soon as each new application arrives.'=>'You\'ll receive an email as soon as each new application arrives.','You\'ll receive one daily digest of applications awaiting your vote.'=>'You\'ll receive one daily digest of applications awaiting your vote.','You\'ll start receiving the newsletter once you confirm below.'=>'You\'ll start receiving the newsletter once you confirm below.','You\'re all set — the community can now review your application and vote.'=>'You\'re all set — the community can now review your application and vote.','You\'re all set — the newsletter will land in your inbox from now on.'=>'You\'re all set — the newsletter will land in your inbox from now on.','You\'re invited'=>'You\'re invited','You\'re invited to join %s'=>'You\'re invited to join %s','You\'ve left %s'=>'You\'ve left %s','you@example.com'=>'you@example.com','Your %s has been removed.'=>'Your %s has been removed.','Your account and everything you published on %s have been permanently deleted. Nothing tied to you is stored here anymore.'=>'Your account and everything you published on %s have been permanently deleted. Nothing tied to you is stored here anymore.','Your application to %s'=>'Your application to %s','Your application will open for community review once you confirm below.'=>'Your application will open for community review once you confirm below.','Your artwork has been removed from the gallery.'=>'Your artwork has been removed from the gallery.','Your biography has been published.'=>'Your biography has been published.','Your biography has been removed.'=>'Your biography has been removed.','Your biography, statement, and portfolio link were erased. Your email address was kept on file — your account is currently banned, and it\'s the only way this site can continue to enforce that.'=>'Your biography, statement, and portfolio link were erased. Your email address was kept on file — your account is currently banned, and it\'s the only way this site can continue to enforce that.','Your current titles:'=>'Your current titles:','Your email address'=>'Your email address','Your gallery:'=>'Your gallery:','Your Join application form is public — anyone can submit an application, and a submitted (and confirmed) application still emails every admitted artist and admin. Right now the only thing standing between that form and an automated bot is a fixed 5-submissions-per-minute-per-IP limit, which a distributed bot can work around entirely. Add a Cloudflare Turnstile site key and secret key above to require human verification on both the Join form and the Newsletter Subscribe form.'=>'Your Join application form is public — anyone can submit an application, and a submitted (and confirmed) application still emails every admitted artist and admin. Right now the only thing standing between that form and an automated bot is a fixed 5-submissions-per-minute-per-IP limit, which a distributed bot can work around entirely. Add a Cloudflare Turnstile site key and secret key above to require human verification on both the Join form and the Newsletter Subscribe form.','Your membership application/account is still active. To remove this data, use the "leave the network" link from any Agnosis email, or ask an administrator.'=>'Your membership application/account is still active. To remove this data, use the "leave the network" link from any Agnosis email, or ask an administrator.','Your membership at %1$s has been temporarily suspended until %2$s.'=>'Your membership at %1$s has been temporarily suspended until %2$s.','Your membership at %s has been reinstated'=>'Your membership at %s has been reinstated','Your membership at %s has been suspended'=>'Your membership at %s has been suspended','Your membership at %s has been suspended.'=>'Your membership at %s has been suspended.','Your message may be reviewed by an automated content filter before being sent to the artist.'=>'Your message may be reviewed by an automated content filter before being sent to the artist.','Your message to the community had no subject or message text that could be found — this often happens when an email client sends an HTML-only message with no plain-text version included. It was not sent to anyone.'=>'Your message to the community had no subject or message text that could be found — this often happens when an email client sends an HTML-only message with no plain-text version included. It was not sent to anyone.','Your message to the community was %1$d characters long — the current limit is %2$d. It was not sent to anyone.'=>'Your message to the community was %1$d characters long — the current limit is %2$d. It was not sent to anyone.','Your name'=>'Your name','Your name (optional)'=>'Your name (optional)','Your previous submission is saved in your submissions page in case you want to review what was sent.'=>'Your previous submission is saved in your submissions page in case you want to review what was sent.','Your submission has been processed. Here\'s what our AI curator came up with — take a look and let us know if it\'s ready to publish.'=>'Your submission has been processed. Here\'s what our AI curator came up with — take a look and let us know if it\'s ready to publish.','Your submissions:'=>'Your submissions:','Your temporary suspension at %s has ended and your membership has been reinstated. You can now log in and submit work as before.'=>'Your temporary suspension at %s has ended and your membership has been reinstated. You can now log in and submit work as before.','Your vote will be recorded once you confirm below.'=>'Your vote will be recorded once you confirm below.','— None (inline message only) —'=>'— None (inline message only) —','— Not set —'=>'— Not set —','…and %d more.'=>'…and %d more.' . "\0" . '…and %d more.','← Newer'=>'← Newer','⚠ %d bounce'=>'⚠ %d bounce' . "\0" . '⚠ %d bounces','⚠ Use only as a temporary workaround when your mail server\'s certificate is not yet trusted (e.g. Plesk self-signed cert before Let\'s Encrypt is applied to the mail daemon). Disable this once the mail server presents a valid certificate.'=>'⚠ Use only as a temporary workaround when your mail server\'s certificate is not yet trusted (e.g. Plesk self-signed cert before Let\'s Encrypt is applied to the mail daemon). Disable this once the mail server presents a valid certificate.','✦ Agnosis Gallery Overview — rendered on the server'=>'✦ Agnosis Gallery Overview — rendered on the server','💡 Quick tips for a great artwork photo'=>'💡 Quick tips for a great artwork photo','💡 This looked like a reply or forward — we found and used your own text (or attachment) above the quoted part. Next time, starting a brand new email to the same address works best.'=>'💡 This looked like a reply or forward — we found and used your own text (or attachment) above the quoted part. Next time, starting a brand new email to the same address works best.','📄 This was published as a new post'=>'📄 This was published as a new post','📬 Vote digest mode'=>'📬 Vote digest mode','📷 Photo enhanced automatically'=>'📷 Photo enhanced automatically','📷 Photo quality score: %d / 10'=>'📷 Photo quality score: %d / 10','📷 Photo quality score: %d/10'=>'📷 Photo quality score: %d/10','🔇 Broadcasts muted'=>'🔇 Broadcasts muted','🔗 A link was not included'=>'🔗 A link was not included' . "\0" . '🔗 Some links were not included']];
